    "# Refinery Blending & Arbitrage Optimizer\n",
    "**Bridging Process Simulation with Quantitative Operations Research**\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook integrates chemical process simulation with mathematical optimization to model dynamic refinery blending economics. It establishes a headless `.NET` bridge to **DWSIM** to extract steady-state thermodynamic data from simulated blendstocks (Naphtha, Reformate, Alkylate, Butane). \n",
    "\n",
    "Using real-time market proxy pricing generated via `yfinance` and non-linear constraint conversion (Linearized RVP), the engine feeds this data into a **SciPy Linear Programming** algorithm. The model calculates the minimum-cost volume mix that satisfies strict USGC Regular 87 constraints and outputs a theoretical arbitrage margin and commercial trade execution signal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1763f654",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Section 1: DWSIM Automation & Bridge Verification\n",
    "This execution block establishes the foundation of the pipeline by connecting Python to the DWSIM process simulator. \n",
    "\n",
    "Instead of relying on static spreadsheets, we use the `pythonnet` library to access DWSIM's `Automation3` headless engine. We programmatically load the chemical flowsheet (`.dwxmz`), force the thermodynamic solver to calculate the physical states of our blendstocks, and extract the material stream objects directly into Python's memory. The block concludes by querying a live thermodynamic property (Temperature) to verify the data bridge is active."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "3977c1a8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "# SECTION 1: DWSIM AUTOMATION & BRIDGE VERIFICATION\n",
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "import clr\n",
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"1. Initializing DWSIM Engine...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Point Python to your DWSIM directory \n",
    "dwsim_path = r\"C:\\Users\\...\\AppData\\Local\\DWSIM\"\n",
    "sys.path.append(dwsim_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Load the DWSIM Libraries (Using Automation3 headless engine to avoid UI thread crashes)\n",
    "clr.AddReference(\"DWSIM.Automation\")\n",
    "from DWSIM.Automation import Automation3\n",
    "\n",
    "# Initialize engine and load your specific flowsheet\n",
    "interf = Automation3()\n",
    "flowsheet_path = r\"C:\\Users\\...\\Quantitative-Refinery-Blending-Commercial-Arbitrage\Blending_Model.dwxmz\"\n",
    "flowsheet = interf.LoadFlowsheet(flowsheet_path)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"2. Flowsheet loaded successfully! Calculating physical states...\")\n",
    "interf.CalculateFlowsheet2(flowsheet)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract stream objects AND cast them to specific Material Streams\n",
    "naphtha = flowsheet.GetFlowsheetSimulationObject(\"Straight-run Naphtha\").GetAsObject()\n",
    "reformate = flowsheet.GetFlowsheetSimulationObject(\"Reformate\").GetAsObject()\n",
    "alkylate = flowsheet.GetFlowsheetSimulationObject(\"Alkylate\").GetAsObject()\n",
    "butane = flowsheet.GetFlowsheetSimulationObject(\"Butane\").GetAsObject()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract dynamic temperatures (K) to verify connection is working\n",
    "t_naphtha = naphtha.GetPhase(\"Mixture\").Properties.temperature\n",
    "print(f\"   -> Bridge Verified: Straight-run Naphtha operating at {t_naphtha:.2f} K\")"
   ]
  },
