   "source": [
    "### Section 2: Dynamic Market Pricing & Quantitative Proxies\n",
    "Because real-time physical market data for intermediate chemical streams (like Alkylate or Reformate) is highly illiquid and paywalled by Price Reporting Agencies, this section implements a quantitative proxy pricing model. \n",
    "\n",
    "Using the `yfinance` API, the script scrapes live NYMEX futures data for **WTI Crude Oil** and **RBOB Gasoline**. It then applies historically weighted crack-spread multipliers to these baselines to dynamically generate a synthetic, real-time spot price array for our four blendstocks. This ensures the downstream optimizer is always reacting to live macroeconomic energy trends rather than static data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "883cf56e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "# SECTION 2: REAL-TIME MARKET PRICING (YFINANCE PROXY)\n",
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "import yfinance as yf\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fetching real-time commodity futures...\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 1. Fetch live data and cast it explicitly to standard Python floats\n",
    "wti_data = yf.Ticker(\"CL=F\").history(period=\"2d\")\n",
    "live_wti_bbl = float(wti_data['Close'].iloc[-1])\n",
    "\n",
    "rbob_data = yf.Ticker(\"RB=F\").history(period=\"2d\")\n",
    "live_rbob_bbl = float(rbob_data['Close'].iloc[-1] * 42)  # Convert $/gal to $/bbl\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Live WTI Crude: ${live_wti_bbl:.2f}/bbl\")\n",
    "print(f\"Live RBOB Gasoline: ${live_rbob_bbl:.2f}/bbl\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2. Generate Spot Prices Array (Clean standard floats)\n",
    "spot_prices = [\n",
    "    round(live_wti_bbl * 1.05, 2),     # Naphtha\n",
    "    round(live_rbob_bbl * 1.08, 2),    # Reformate\n",
    "    round(live_rbob_bbl * 1.12, 2),    # Alkylate\n",
    "    round(live_wti_bbl * 0.60, 2)      # Butane\n",
    "]\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Spot Price Array Loaded: {spot_prices}\")"
   ]
  },
