    "### Section 3: LIMS Database Integration & Constraint Linearization\n",
    "In a physical refinery, empirical combustion metrics like RON and RVP cannot be generated by thermodynamic equations of state; they are tested by chemists and stored in a Laboratory Information Management System (LIMS). This block uses `pandas` to simulate querying a LIMS database to extract the latest stream assays.\n",
    "\n",
    "Crucially, because Reid Vapor Pressure (RVP) does not blend linearly in the real world, this section applies an industry-standard power law ($RVP^{1.25}$) to convert the non-linear physical vapor pressures into linear blending indices. This mathematical transformation is required before feeding the constraints into the linear programming matrix."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "6d93a186",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "# SECTION 3: LIMS DATABASE INTEGRATION & CONSTRAINT LINEARIZATION\n",
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import math\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Fetching Assay Data from LIMS Database...\")\n",
    "# Read the CSV file\n",
    "lims_db = pd.read_csv(r\"C:\\Users\\...\\Quantitative-Refinery-Blending-Commercial-Arbitrage\\refinery_lims_data.csv\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Extract as lists directly from the dataframe\n",
    "assay_ron = lims_db['RON'].tolist()\n",
    "assay_rvp_psi = lims_db['RVP_psi'].tolist()\n",
    "\n",
    "# Linearize RVP dynamically\n",
    "rvp_indices = [math.pow(rvp, 1.25) for rvp in assay_rvp_psi]\n",
    "print(\"LIMS Data successfully loaded into optimizer matrix.\")"
   ]
  },
