    "### Section 4: Linear Programming Optimizer Engine\n",
    "This section defines the core mathematical engine of the project. It formulates the physical blending parameters into a strict Linear Programming (LP) matrix to be solved via standard operations research techniques. \n",
    "\n",
    "The function constructs the **Objective Function** to minimize the total blend cost, bounded by a rigid multidimensional \"feasible region\" composed of three constraint sets:\n",
    "* **Inequality Constraints ($A_{ub} x \\le b_{ub}$):** Enforces the minimum **87.0** RON limit (multiplied by -1 to fit the standard $\\le$ matrix format) and caps the maximum linearized RVP index.\n",
    "* **Equality Constraints ($A_{eq} x = b_{eq}$):** Guarantees mass balance by forcing the sum of all volumetric fractions to equal exactly **1.0** (100% of the barrel).\n",
    "* **Bounds:** Prevents physically impossible scenarios by restricting component use to between **0** and **1.0**.\n",
    "\n",
    "The compiled matrix is fed into SciPy's `linprog` function using the `highs` dual-simplex algorithm, a highly efficient solver standard in commercial optimization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "c92eb022",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "# SECTION 4: LINEAR PROGRAMMING OPTIMIZER ENGINE\n",
    "# =====================================================================\n",
    "\n",
    "from scipy.optimize import linprog\n",
    "\n",
    "def run_blending_optimizer(prices, ron_specs, rvp_idx, inventories, batch_size, target_ron=87.0, target_rvp_max=9.0):\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    Executes a linear programming algorithm to find the minimum-cost volume mix\n",
    "    that satisfies USGC Regular Unleaded 87 specifications.\n",
    "    \"\"\"\n",
    "    num_components = len(prices)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Objective Function: Minimize cost per barrel\n",
    "    c = prices\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Target RVP must also be linearized for the constraint comparison\n",
    "    target_rvp_index = target_rvp_max ** 1.25\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Inequality Constraints (A_ub * x <= b_ub)\n",
    "    # 1. RON: sum(Vol * RON) >= Target RON  -> sum(Vol * -RON) <= -Target RON\n",
    "    # 2. RVP: sum(Vol * RVP_Index) <= Target RVP_Index\n",
    "    A_ub = [\n",
    "        [-ron for ron in ron_specs], \n",
    "        rvp_idx\n",
    "    ]\n",
    "    b_ub = [-target_ron, target_rvp_index]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Equality Constraint (A_eq * x = b_eq)\n",
    "    # Sum of volume fractions must equal exactly 1.0 (100% of the barrel)\n",
    "    A_eq = [[1.0] * num_components]\n",
    "    b_eq = [1.0]\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Bounds: Each stream can constitute between 0% and 100% of the blend\n",
    "    bounds = []\n",
    "    for i in range(num_components):\n",
    "        max_physical_fraction = inventories[i]/batch_size\n",
    "        upper_bound = min(1.0, max_physical_fraction)\n",
    "        bounds.append((0, upper_bound))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Execute the Highs solver via SciPy\n",
    "    result = linprog(c, A_ub=A_ub, b_ub=b_ub, A_eq=A_eq, b_eq=b_eq, bounds=bounds, method='highs')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    if result.success:\n",
    "        return {\n",
    "            \"status\": \"Optimal Solution Found\",\n",
    "            \"cost_per_barrel\": round(result.fun, 2),\n",
    "            \"volumes\": [round(x, 4) for x in result.x],\n",
    "            \"bounds_used\": bounds,\n",
    "            # Extracting Shadow Prices (Dual Values)\n",
    "            \"shadow_prices\": {\n",
    "                \"rvp_constraint\": result.ineqlin.marginals[1], \n",
    "                \"tank_limits\": result.upper.marginals\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        return {\"status\": \"Infeasible\", \"message\": result.message}"
   ]
  },
